This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in 2011. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authority to the Secretary of State, in coordination with the Secretary of Defense, as conferred by section 1535(c)(1) of the Ike Skelton National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2011. The delegated function is to make a specified report to the Committees on Armed Services, Foreign Relations, and Appropriations of the Senate and the Committees on Armed Services, Foreign Affairs, and Appropriations of the House of Representatives. The memorandum also authorizes the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.